hook.real_world_problem:
Compare AI integration approaches:

```java
// SPRING AI (what you've learned):
@Service
class PaymentAI {
    private final ChatClient chatClient;
    PaymentAI(ChatClient.Builder b) {
        chatClient = b.defaultSystem("You are Razorpay AI.").build();
    }
    String answer(String q) {
        return chatClient.prompt().user(q).call().content();
    }
}

// LANGCHAIN4J (just an interface — LangChain4j generates the implementation!):
interface PaymentAI {
    @SystemMessage("You are Razorpay AI assistant.")
    String answer(@UserMessage String question);
}
// LangChain4j generates the whole implementation:
PaymentAI ai = AiServices.create(PaymentAI.class, chatModel);
ai.answer("What is Razorpay?"); // works!
```

Difference: LangChain4j's AiServices = declare interface → get AI service.
Spring AI: manual wiring of ChatClient. Both are valid; knowing both makes you versatile.

concept_explanation.ai_services:
**LangChain4j AiServices — the interface magic:**

```java
// 1. Define as an interface:
@AiService
interface RazorpaySupportAI {
    @SystemMessage("""
        You are Razorpay's customer support AI.
        Help merchants with payment integration questions.
        Be concise and technical. Suggest docs links when relevant.
        """)
    String answer(@UserMessage String question);

    // Multi-turn with memory:
    @SystemMessage("You are Razorpay AI with conversation history.")
    String chat(@UserMessage String message, @MemoryId String sessionId);
}

// 2. Register as Spring Bean (with Spring Boot integration):
@Configuration
class LangChain4jConfig {
    @Bean
    RazorpaySupportAI razorpaySupportAI(ChatLanguageModel model, ChatMemoryProvider memProvider) {
        return AiServices.builder(RazorpaySupportAI.class)
            .chatLanguageModel(model)
            .chatMemoryProvider(memProvider)  // per-session memory
            .build();
    }

    @Bean
    ChatMemoryProvider chatMemoryProvider() {
        return memoryId -> MessageWindowChatMemory.withMaxMessages(10);
    }
}

// 3. Inject and use — just like any other Spring Bean:
@Service
class SupportController {
    private final RazorpaySupportAI ai;
    public String handleTicket(String sessionId, String message) {
        return ai.chat(message, sessionId); // memory managed per sessionId!
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.rag_l4j:
**LangChain4j RAG:**

```java
// RAG in LangChain4j:
EmbeddingStore<TextSegment> store = new InMemoryEmbeddingStore<>();
EmbeddingModel embeddingModel = AnthropicEmbeddingModel.withApiKey(apiKey);

// Ingest documents:
Document doc = Document.from("Razorpay webhook retries 5 times over 24 hours.");
DocumentSplitter splitter = DocumentSplitters.recursive(500, 50);
List<TextSegment> segments = splitter.split(doc);
embeddingModel.embedAll(segments).forEach((segment, embedding) ->
    store.add(embedding, segment));

// RAG-enabled AI service:
ContentRetriever retriever = EmbeddingStoreContentRetriever.builder()
    .embeddingStore(store)
    .embeddingModel(embeddingModel)
    .maxResults(3)
    .minScore(0.7)
    .build();

RazorpayDocsAI docsAI = AiServices.builder(RazorpayDocsAI.class)
    .chatLanguageModel(model)
    .contentRetriever(retriever)  // RAG enabled!
    .build();
```

